name: Reynolds Creek
description:
Introduction

This is a challenging and unique hike and canyoning experience around Mount Bangalore in the Main Range National Park.

The route includes an off-trail bushbash in the beginning, followed by some short abseils down waterfalls in Reynolds Creek, and another off-trail bushbash to exit. The terrain in Reynolds Creek is great and definitely the highlight of the route, but comes at a price for access and exit requirements. Ropes are necessary to descend the two waterfalls safely and the route is best done as shown in clockwise direction
